Brazil Inflation to Ease 1.5 Points by April, Tombini Says

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   R a g i r
-- 
2011-09-29T13:08:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/brazil-inflation-to-ease-1-5-points-by-april-tombini-says.html
Brazil ’s inflation rate will ease
by at least 1.5 percentage points by April, central bank
President Alexandre Tombini said.  Twelve-month inflation is on a downward trajectory and will
begin to slow in the fourth quarter of this year as the full
effect of the bank’s interest-rate increases is felt, Tombini
said at an event in Curitiba.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Ragir in Rio de Janeiro at 
 aragir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Harry Maurer at 
